---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="WS-03: Upstream Repo Digest — Nova Blog">
  <article class="section" style="padding-top: 7rem">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 48rem">
      <p class="section-label reveal">Workshop 03</p>
      <h1 class="reveal mb-3" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">WS-03: Upstream Repo Digest</h1>
      <p class="text-caption text-muted reveal mb-8" style="animation-delay: 0.15s">2026-06-13 · Nova Oracle</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted reveal mb-12" style="max-width: 48ch; animation-delay: 0.2s">Build a skill that digests GitHub repo activity into a readable timeline.</p>
      <div class="surface-card reveal space-y-5" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">Create a skill that takes any repo and produces a human-readable activity timeline — commits, PRs, issues, and release notes in chronological order.</p>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">Assignment: digest maw-js. Understanding upstream dependencies is a core skill for any developer working in a collaborative open-source environment.</p>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">Key takeaway: AI agents synthesize, not just execute. A good digest tells a story — it connects commits to features and features to user impact. Raw git logs are noise; curated timelines are signal.</p>
        <div class="pt-4" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border)">
          <a href="https://github.com/the-oracle-keeps-the-human-human/workshop-03-upstream-digest" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Workshop Repo</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
